<HEADLINE>
CHIAYI `TEA AMBASSADORS' TO PROMOTE TEA IN SINGAPORE, MALAYSIA
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Jan. 9 (CNA) 01/09/07  21:43:58 (By T.C. Jiang)
</P>
<P>
Twelve "tea ambassadors" -- students from Shiding elementary
school in southern Chiayi County -- will visit Singapore and
Malaysia Jan. 28-Feb. 1 to promote the county's tea culture and
industry, county officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The students visited Chiayi County Magistrate Chen Ming-wen, who
presented awards to the students and their instructors. He
encouraged the students to use the trip to let the world know
that Chiayi County produces top quality tea.
</P>
<P>
School Principal Chen Ruey-cheng said third-to-six grade students
have two classes each week on choosing and making quality tea and
share their research results on personal web pages.
</P>
<P>
According to Chen, the school was also selected by the Ministry
of Education as a model for integrating learning and teaching
with Information and Communication Technology.
</P>
